status_message: We're moms, and we get it. Finding affordable and convenient learning programs for your kids can be tough! status_message:
The notion that "family planning" is inaccessible whatsoever to anyone in this country is absurd.  There are drugstores and grocery stores EVERYWHERE which carry a plethora of contraception options, many of which are less than $10.  We are ALL FOR easy access to contraception.  

But what you mean, Ms. Crocker, is abortion.  And that you and other liberal feminists refuse to call it by name, preferring instead to use generic terms like "family planning" is telling.  When you write, "As feminists, we care about all families and about constructively discussing the best ways to make sure all families thrive" you forgot to finish that sentence in a truthful way.  What Planned Parenthood always means is, "we care about all families and about constructively discussing the best ways to make sure all families thrive, even if it means killing off some of them."

Because that's what you do, after all.  And many of the babies you kill?  They're females.  

So you'll have to excuse our laughter at the ridiculousness of our having our column responded to by the CEO of an organization which happily gobbles up millions of taxpayer dollars annually (45% of your revenues, in fact!), performs increasing numbers of abortions annually, and then complains about OUR view of feminism.  

Whether women wear scrubs, aprons, hairnets, OR stilettos to their jobs, they have our respect for trying to make their own way.  Which was the point of our piece to begin with.  ~Mock
link_name: Planned Parenthood CEO: Chicks on the Right wrong about feminism

Attention Townspeople!

This weekend is a big one for our main site: http://chicksontheright.com/. We have launched an all-new redesign simultaneously with switching to a new hosting provider.

There will DEFINITELY be some odd things happening over the next few days while the new host updates throughout the entire Internet (it can take up to 72 hours). Some of you will see the new version of the site immediately while others may not see it for a few days. We are going to do our best to keep any new posts up on both hosts so that everyone can still see what's going on; however any comments made on the site will not save unless you are on the new version. If you see a "404" error when trying to view one of our posts, please just type chicksontheright.com into your browser and you should have no trouble locating the post from there.

Please bear with us as there will undoubtedly be some hiccups over the next few days. We have people working tirelessly behind the scenes to get everything working correctly.  Make sure to CLEAN YOUR BROWSER CACHE AND COOKIES!!!

Also, all the old login and commenting functionality is BACK! Please register if you have never done so and make sure to email webmaster@chicksontheright.com with any problems.

ATTENTION TOWNSPEOPLE! Are you a college student looking for a great internship opportunity starting immediately? Do you know a great conservative college kid who might want to add "Chicks On The Right Intern" to their resume? Daisy and I are looking for 1-2 interns to help us starting immediately for as many hours per week as available (ideally 15-20 but we're flexible) and for as long as available to do some project work for us.

1. Conservative through and through. NO EXCEPTIONS.

Owner of a smart phone, and willing to respond to emails/texts from us (even if just to ACKNOWLEDGE our messages) within 4 hours between 7am-9pm (exceptions on some days can be made in advance if necessary) – this should be a piece of cake for college kids today – since you're all basically physically fused to your smartphones anyway.

Daisy's overall analysis:  I think Mitt owned this one. He doesn't talk in circles like Obama does. Obama has no record.  Consequently, Obama's in the difficult position now, and I believe it shows. I agree with Mock that Obama's performance was better than last time, but the only direction he had to go from two weeks ago was, well, UP.  

And on a total side note - this whole "undecided voters" thing?  These people need to get lives and strap on a set already.  If you don't know who you're voting for by now, then you're either a complete moron or a lying sack of crap.  This is the clearest choice between two very different sets of policies/ideals that I've seen in my adult life. I'll go on a limb here and say that the majority of the "undecideds" in the audience are liberals pretending to be undecided so they could ask a stupid question at a Town Hall on national television.  

Undecided, my butt.

End rant.
